Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.03,0:00:06.19,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,In 1912, fragments from a\Ngravel pit
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.19,0:00:09.90,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,in Sussex seemed to give\NBritish science
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:11.75,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,the fossil it wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.75,0:00:13.22,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,A human-like skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:14.69,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,An ape-like jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.69,0:00:17.09,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,A famous name: Piltdown\NMan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:20.29,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The evidence was thin, but\Nthe story
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.29,0:00:22.08,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,was powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.08,0:00:23.88,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,It fit a brain-first\Ntheory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:26.59,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,and gave Britain its own\Nancient ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.44,0:00:30.11,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Some anatomists doubted\Nthe skull and jaw
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:31.45,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,belonged together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.45,0:00:32.79,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,But access was limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.79,0:00:35.39,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,prestige was heavy, and\Nthe specimen kept
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:36.91,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,circulating as authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.91,0:00:38.43,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The fraud was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:39.43,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,not perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.43,0:00:40.44,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,It was welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.42,0:00:45.32,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,By 1953, tests exposed the\Ntrick.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.32,0:00:47.19,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The skull was recent human\Nbone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.99,0:00:49.54,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The jaw was from an\Norangutan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:51.50,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The teeth had been filed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.11,0:00:53.39,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The bones had been\Nstained.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:00:56.23,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The hoax survived because\Nit let the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.23,0:00:57.79,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,field feel correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.79,0:00:59.35,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The mystery fades.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.98,0:01:01.32,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The receipts remain.
